-- Andean Development Bank Agrees $100 Million 4-Year Loan With Asian Banks
-- Takashi Ueno
-- 2010-08-06T06:06:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/andean-development-bank-agrees-100-million-4-year-loan-with-asian-banks.html

          
          
             Corp. Andina de Fomento, the
Venezuelan development bank known as CAF, agreed to borrow $100
million over four years from a group of banks led by Mizuho
Corporate Bank Ltd., according to the Tokyo-based lender.  
 The other lenders include the Bank of Taiwan, Chang Hwa
Commercial Bank, Taiwan Cooperative Bank and Land Bank of
Taiwan, said  Gaku Deguchi , a Mizuho spokesman.  
